<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Veranso-Libalah &amp; G. Kadereit" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Argyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Argyrella richardsiae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="richardsiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Argyrella richardsiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. bambutorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambutorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. bambutorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by having serrulate leaf margins, intersepalar appendages absent, and stamens dimorphic (versus entire leaf margins, intersepalar appendages present, and stamens isomorphic in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. bambutorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambutorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. bambutorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species also differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. amplexicaulis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplexicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. amplexicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. sessilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. sessilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hutch. ex Brenan &amp; Keay) Veranso-Libalah &amp; G.Kadereit and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. angolensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angolensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. angolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its many new branches or buds arising at each node (versus unbranched in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. amplexicaulis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplexicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. amplexicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. sessilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. sessilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. angolensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angolensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. angolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Veranso-Libalah &amp; G. Kadereit" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Argyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Argyrella richardsiae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="richardsiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Argyrella richardsiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has broadly ovate leaves versus lanceolate to linear in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harv" authorityYear="1868" baseAuthorityName="E. Mey. ex Graham" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Argyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Argyrella canescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Argyrella canescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. linearis" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">A. linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jacq.-
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fél">Fel</normalizedToken>
.) Veranso-Libalah &amp; G.Kadereit. Also, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. richardsiae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="richardsiae">
